    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Assist Rails</title>
        <para>Assist rails are located at the entry step along the left front bulkhead wall (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700441">Fig. 41, item 3</hotlnk>). The rails are installed to assist ingress and egress of
            the passengers. An optional assist handrail is located on the forward bulkhead (
            <hotlnk document="s47004_40.xml" xrefid="f4700442">Fig. 42, Item 3</hotlnk>) below the windshield and dash
            board extension panel.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700441" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700441.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 41. Step Well Assist Rails</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FRONT CRASH BARRIER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ENTRY DOOR</callout1>
                <callout1>3. STEP WELL ASSIST HAND RAIL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
